President Donald J. Trump has announced additional members of the White House Counsel's Office. The appointees include Greg Katsas, who serves as Deputy Assistant to the President and Deputy Counsel to the President; Makan Delrahim, who serves as Deputy Assistant to the President and Deputy Counsel to the President; Annie Donaldson, who serves as Deputy Assistant to the President, Special Counsel to the President, and Chief of Staff for the Office of the White House Counsel; John Eisenberg, who serves as Deputy Assistant to the President, National Security Council Legal Advisor, and Deputy Counsel to the President for National Security Affairs; Stefan Passantino, who serves as Deputy Assistant to the President and Deputy Counsel to the President; Jim Carroll, who serves as Special Assistant to the President and Senior Counsel to the President; Stacy Cline Amin, who serves as Special Assistant to the President and Associate Counsel to the President; Rene Augustine, who serves as Special Assistant to the President and Senior Associate Counsel to the President; John Bash, who serves as Special Assistant to the President and Associate Counsel to the President; James Burnham, who serves as Special Assistant to the President and Senior Associate Counsel to the President; Jed Doty, who serves as Associate Counsel to the President; Uttam Dhillon, who serves as Special Assistant to the President and Senior Associate Counsel to the President; Michael Ellis, who serves as Special Assistant to the President, Senior Associate Counsel to the President, and Deputy National Security Council Legal Advisor; Daniel Epstein, who serves as Associate Counsel to the President; Scott Gast, who serves as Special Assistant to the President and Senior Associate Counsel to the President; Chris Grieco, who serves as Associate Counsel to the President; Rob Luther, who serves as Associate Counsel to the President; Stuart McCommas, who serves as Deputy Associate Counsel to the President; Mike McGinley, who serves as Associate Counsel to the President; John Moran, who serves as Associate Counsel to the President; David Morrell, who serves as Associate Counsel to the President; Claire Murray, who serves as Associate Counsel to the President; Brian Rabbitt, who serves as Associate Counsel to the President; Schuyler Schouten, who serves as Special Assistant to the President and Associate Counsel to the President; James Schultz, who serves as Special Assistant to the President and Senior Associate Counsel to the President; John Walk, who serves as Associate Counsel to the President.